Perhaps a better solution would be a hybrid of both ideas. Something along the lines of titlehref=&quot;#foo&quot; ... &lt;foot&gt;&lt;div id=&quot;foo&quot;&gt;&lt;img ...<br /><br />Only problem is the &lt;foot&gt; will not be backwards compatible and would show up in the body in older browsers (display:none can fix the appearance, but it will still be in the body in the DOM).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=377">lyosha</a> — Fri Jan 23, 2009 1:30 am</p><hr />
