Linebreaks in tooltips is already supported in the spec.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/multipage/dom.html#the-title-attribute">http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/cu ... -attribute</a><!-- m --><br /><br />As for rich content in tooltips, I think it has been discussed on the list but I don't have a pointer currently. I don't think your specific proposal would work though (what if you want the tooltip to be the string &quot;url(#foo)&quot; for instance?), but maybe a new attribute would work (e.g. titlehtml=&quot;foo &lt;img&gt; ...&quot;, albeit ugly and would probably have to be different in XHTML).<br /><br />The spec contains suggestions for how to do footnotes, which could be presented as tooltips with JS+CSS if desired.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/multipage/text-level-semantics.html#footnotes">http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/cu ... #footnotes</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4">zcorpan</a> — Wed Jan 21, 2009 6:16 pm</p><hr />
